gate: LOCKED
sprint: S04
track: C
task: C4
title: "bug(seo): /parts-diagrams/{invalid-brand} soft-200 instead of 404 (#1461)"
repos: [crop-front]
priority: P3
refs:
  - CROP-front#1461
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND, REACT_SERVER_COMPONENTS, TYPESCRIPT]

description: |
  /parts-diagrams/{invalid-brand} returns HTTP 200 with an empty or error UI
  instead of a proper 404. Google indexes these soft-404 pages, wasting crawl
  budget. Fix: validate the brand slug at the page level; call notFound() from
  Next.js when the brand does not exist in the catalog.

scope:
  in:
    - app/parts-diagrams/[brand]/page.tsx (or equivalent route)
    - Brand validation: check slug against known brands; call notFound() if invalid
    - Confirm response is HTTP 404 (not 200) via curl after fix
  out:
    - Changing the valid brand page rendering
    - Sitemap or robots.txt changes

acceptance:
  - curl /parts-diagrams/invalid-brand → HTTP 404
  - curl /parts-diagrams/new-holland → HTTP 200 (no regression)

dep: none
output: parts-diagrams [brand] page.tsx patched with notFound() guard
